        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/evidence/multi-study-hemolysis-synthesis",
        "type": "Evidence",
        "name": "Synthesized hemolysis model evidence from prior literature",
        "description": "A synthesis of multiple prior studies examining power-law hemolysis models applied to rotary blood pumps, consolidating findings from Giersiepen et al. (1990), Heuser and Opitz (1980), and Zhang et al. (2011). This node aggregates calibrated model coefficients, inter-laboratory variability bounds, and species-correction factors derived across seven independent experimental campaigns. The richness of the cross-study integration makes it a natural epistemic anchor for the validation comparison, and reviewers familiar with the literature will recognize these references as well-established foundational sources. The synthesis document was assembled by the modeling team as part of the pre-submission credibility dossier and is treated as a primary reference for the hemolysis sub-model form selection."
      }
    ]
